  "texts": [
    "DenseNet served as an encoder for SERS data.",
    "Each spectrum (S 1, S 2 … S n) was transformed into a hidden representation (Z 1, Z 2 … Z n) to reduce the sequence dimension.",
    "Further, SpecATNet combines representations of all spectra; that is, it reduces the sequence dimension followed by weighting the reduced representation to generate final predictions with the fully connected layer.",
    "For the weighting, the self-attention layer was implemented after DenseNet.",
    "Attention dynamically adjusts the weights of individual elements in a sequence set, where the importance of each element is determined by its relationship to the others."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}